inn1.comm: wide outside the off stump, left alone
bit fuller from Franklin, Gilchrist drives well through covers to the deep
pitched up and swinging away, driven well by Hayden wide of mid off to the deep
short and wide outside the off stump, Gilchrist puts it away in style, slashes it over backward-point, one bounce into the fence
good ball this time from Franklin, held its line, Hayden covers the line and lets it go
another ball outside the off stump, Hayden watches it and lets it go through to McCullum
good ball on target, 142 km/h, worked to the on side
short delivery, gets a thick bottom edge to fine leg, looking for the pull
back of a length delivery, moves slightly away from Hayden, who defends to the off side
right back and pushes back down the track, 143.3 km/h
oversteps, fuller outside the off stump, Gilchrist mistimes the drive to mid off
gets the edge, just to the right of Fleming at first slip, that was too close to body for the cut shot
left alone outside the off stump
pitched up delivery outside the off stump, driven straight along the ground to Vettori at mid off
on the legs, Hayden gets an inside edge onto the body and then to fine leg, comes back for the second run
looking to leave it alone, gets the edge along the ground to backward-point
gets behind a back of a length delivery and pushes to point
squares up Hayden, good delivery from Bond
moves into line and lets it go outside the off stump through to McCullum
beats Hayden, bit fuller and swinging away, looking to drive straight down the ground, misses it
back of a length delivery, Gilchrist on the back foot defends to point
pitched up and wide outside the off stump, Gilchrist puts it away, driven through covers to the fence
gets back and nudges to the on side
wide outside the off stump, cut away hard in the air, bounces just short of Patel at backward-point
well directed from Franklin, moves back and works to the on side
pitched from Franklin, it was in the slot, lofts it straight past the bowler to the fence
works it through midwicket to the deep
quick single to short cover, Vettori runs in from mid off to field the ball
plays to the on side
full on the legs, tucked away nicely to long leg fence, bad line from Bond, probably looking for the yorker
on the pads once again, tucks it through midwicket
bit slower from Bond, 131 km/h, left alone, on the second bounce to McCullum
half-volley outside the off stump, driven well through extra-cover, places it well to the fence
nudges wide of mid on for a single
pitched up delivery, driven back to the bowler
mistimes the drive to mid on, looking for the big booming drive
oversteps, drifts down the leg side
lets the ball go outside the off stump, was thinking of the cut shot
once again lets it go through to McCullum, a watchful Hayden
on the middle stump, pushes to the on side
driven to mid off, fielded by Vettori
pushes upishly to backward-point to the right of Patel who dives, just falls short
angled across, left alone outside the off stump, Bond oversteps
on the legs, flicks it behind square leg to the deep, McMillan runs around from fine leg does well to slide and stop it
pitched up delivery outside the off stump, driven to Vettori at mid off, who misfields to allow a run
lovely shot from Gilchrist, driven wide of mid on, the ball races to the fence, brings up the 50 for Australia in quick time
nudges to midwicket to pick up a single
pitched outside the leg stump, loud appeal, given not out by umpire Rauf, they scamper through for a leg bye
this time on the pads, looking to glance it fine, misses, off the thigh pad to the fence
left alone outside the off stump
lofts it in the air over wide mid on to the fence, good shot
defends to the on side
moves back and defends to the off side
good ball almost squares up Gilchrist, pushes upto mid off
149.9 km/h, fuller delivery driven to mid off
good shot for maximum, flicks it in the air over backward square leg fence
defends with a straight bat back down the track
slower from Bond, 128.6 km/h, defends to the off side
moves back and works to the on side for a single
good ball, beaten by the turn, pitches outside the leg stump, spins across, off the pad to the off side
this time watchfully moves forward and pushes to backward-point
good ball, pushes to short extra-cover
moves back and defends with a straight bat back to the bowler
gets back and cuts to deep point for a single
great shot from Gilchrist, driven well in the gap between extra-cover and mid off, the ball races to the fence in quick time
goes for the pull and misses, goes just over, closer to the off stump
looking to work it through the on side, off the pad
moves back and works it off his pads in front of square leg for a single
143.6 km/h, looking to play through the on side, misses, off the pad
back of a length delivery, defended to midwicket
tossed up bit fuller outside the off stump, driven well down the ground to long off
pitched outside the leg stump, plays it in the air through midwicket
moves forward and defends to cover, good bowling from Patel
bit slower and fraction short from Patel, cut to deep cover for a single
bit fuller on the middle and leg, driven well down the ground to long on, good running fetches the second run
oversteps, this is bad, moves back and works through midwicket
loud appeal given not out by umpire Rauf, it was pitched outside the leg stump, struck the pad
moves in line and pushes back down the track to Gillespie
Gillespie gets the first break-through, it was short and down the leg side, Hayden looking for the pull, gets the edge through to McCullum (off the glove), who takes the catch.
wide outside the off stump, left alone through to McCullum
once again left alone
on the off stump, driven to cover, not from the middle off the bat
full toss driven back to Patel, drops short of him
comes down the track and drives it back, fielded by Patel
driven to mid on, a quick throw from the fielder, Patel taking evasive action in the back ground as the ball struck the stumps
driven to the right of mid on for a single
comes to the pitch of the delivery and drives to long on for his first run
full toss driven wide of long off for a single
short ball, struck on the body, looking for the pull, misses it
on the leg stump, pushes it back to Gillespie
gets a bottom edge down to thirdman for a single, Gilchrist on 49
oversteps, driven to mid off
short and wide, cut off the back foot to cover fence, nice shot
defends to cover on the front foot
driven well along the ground to mid off
gets his fifty in style, dances down the track and lofts it over mid on to the fence
advances once again and plays to the on side
a big hit over midwicket for maximum, goes out of the stadium, lovely strike, a slog sweep
worked through midwicket
pitches on the middle and straightens, Gilchrist once again looking for the slog sweep, misses it completely, strikes the pad, loud appeal, umpire Rauf takes a long time and then lifts the finger.
moves forward and defends on the track
moves forward and opens the face off the bat and plays to thirdman
a bouncer from Gillespie, ducks under it
wide outside the off stump, left alone through to McCullum
pitched up outside the off stump, Clarke finds the gap to deep cover, Franklin fields it and gives it to Patel, who throws it in
oversteps, pushes to the off side
shoulders arms to a delivery outside the off stump
moves forward in line and defends to cover, a loud call of  "wait on"  from Clarke
comes forward and defends to cover, fielded by Marshall
moves forward once again and defends to the off side
on the off and middle, driven to mid on
moves forward in line and defends to cover, can't get it through the ring
short and flat from Vettori, pushes to the off side
comes forward and defends to the off side.
wide outside the off stump, gets the under-edge, on the bounce to McCullum, who finds it difficult to take, not much of feet movement as he went after the ball.
defended on the back foot to cover
defends to the off side, good line from Gillespie
moves forward and lets it go through to McCullum
runs it down to thirdman to pick up a single
swings it high and one bounce into the midwicket fence, good strike from Ponting, it was in the slot
moves back and prods to the off side
quicker delivery and it was flat, pushed back to Vettori
another flat delivery on the legs, worked to the on side
defended on the front foot to the off side
good ball once again, stretches forward and defends
breaks the shackles, uses his feet well and lofts it over wide mid on to the fence.&
fuller delivery driven to mid off, fielded by Bond
short outside the off stump, Ponting caught in two minds, just puts his bat
times it well to covers, Ross Taylor dives to his right and makes a wonderful stop
driven firmly upto mid off to Bond
it was in the slot outside the off stump, hit straight to Fleming at short cover, who takes the catch.
digs in a short one outside the off stump, left alone through to McCullum
comes forward and quietly plays to the on side
defended to the on side
a touch short, moves back and drives wide of mid off
looking for the cut, chops it onto the ground, that was a close thing
defended back to the bowler
moves forward and defends to the off side
pitched up outside the off stump, driven to cover
on the stumps, worked in front of square leg for a single
looking to drive through the covers, gets the edge down along the ground to thirdman
short delivery, Clarke looking to pull out of a pull shot, gets a top edge and goes in the air to fine leg, Vettori does well to run around and field
a low full toss, driven straight to the fielder at cover, can't get it through the in-field
moves forward and pulls to midwicket fence, it was not off the middle of the bat
down the leg side, signalled wide
driven down the ground to long on
comes forward and watchfully defends on the track
flat delivery outside the off stump, moves back and cuts to backward-point
flatter again, moves back and drives to the left of backward-point, comes quickly back for the second run
dances down the track and and defends it back to the bowler
moves back and cuts well to deep cover, fielded by Gillespie
mistimes the cut to cover
turned in front of square leg for couple of runs
moves forward and defends to the off side
wide outside the off stump, room for Clarke as he cuts to deep backward-point
waits on his back foot and plays it late to thirdman, McMillan does well
again played wonderfully well, cuts it late to thirdman, picks up couple of runs
defended to the on side
wide outside the off stump, cut to deep backward-point
loud shout turned down, going down the leg side
comes forward and defends back down the track
room outside the off stump, cut to deep point
uses his feet and lofts it in the air to long off, falls just short of Patel.
tossed up a fraction wide of off stump, Symonds leans back and runs it fine, sets off for the single, and just manages to beat the fielder's throw
tossed up, down the track waltzes Clarke, getting to the pitch of it and lofting it down the ground for four, top shot!
quicker delivery on the stumps, Clarke comes down the track and drives it to long-on
flighted delivery outside off stump, Symonds kneels down and sweeps it away to backward square leg for a single
short and wide, he rocks back and cuts that into the gap at point, but just the single this time
flatter on the stumps, Symonds shuffles and works it to midwicket
delivery looped outside off stump, Clarke opens the face of the bat and steers it straight to the fielder at gully
full and straight on the stumps, Clarke gets forward and plays it back to the bowler
quicker and flatter, he rocks back and chops to gully
drifts down leg stumps, he turns it around the corner to bring up the 150
tossed up on off stump, Clarke gets forward and pushes to mid-off
flat down the legs, and he flicks it around the corner
short and wide, rubbish ball, and its cut away to deep backward point for one
good length outside off stump with some more lift on it, and he leaves it alone watchfully
slower ball outside off stump, looking for the yorker, which doesnt get that right, and Clarke taps it in front of point for one
short and wide, Symonds opens the face and runs it to gully, where Fleming dives to his left and saves it very well
and again, short of a length and Symonds runs it to a very acrobatic Fleming at gully, good stuff from the skip
good length on the stumps, slower ball, Symonds gets forward and defends
tossed up, he drives to cover
quicker on the stumps, he defends it to the on side
short and wide, cracked out to the deep backward point sweeper
flat on the stumps, Clarke uses the feet well and chips to mid-on for one
shot! Just a fraction short but he cuts that powerfully and in the gap behind square for four
tossed up on off stump, he works that to midwicket
short of a length outside off stump, he opens the face and runs it to third man for one
very short and wide, Clarke thinks about the pull but bails out in his piroutte, and the umpire calls it wide
short and wide again, he pulls but cant connect well, theres an inside edge that bounces before McCullum
hat-trick of lifters outside off stump, to which Clarke once more thinks about the pull but resists

gone! Set him up! Slower ball, just, on a good length outside off stump, Clarke cant contain his aggression and drives at it across the line, getting a leading edge that pops up straight in the air, there's calls of 'CATCH IT' and three men on the off side swoop in, but its Astle, running in from mid-off, who takes the steepler - making a tough chance look easy - and sends Clarke on his way
good length delivery outside off, Symonds gets forward and pushes it straight to the fielder at short cover
good length outside off stump, he stands and defends to the off side
good length outside off stump, Hussey tries the dab to third man but cant beat gully
tossed up on off stump, he tries the flick but cant time it well at all, ball pops up on the leg side but theres no catches in that up close
back of a length delivery on middle and leg, Hussey goes back and flicks it away to midwicket for a single to get off the mark
tossed up outside off stump, he gets forward and drives back to Vettori
tossed up on the stumps, he comes forward and works it to leg but cant beat midwicket
fired in on the legs, and Hussey flicks fine for one
just short of a length outside off stump, Hussey has no room to cut but tries anyways, chopping it in front of point
back of a length outside off stump, up on the toes he goes, running it to point
good length on middle and leg with a little more lift on it, Hussey tries to work it off the hips but gets all tangled up
quicker and a tad fuller on off stump, Hussey tries to manufacture a flick but has to adjust to the pace, and ends up defending back to Bond
back of a length outside off stump, he hops up and runs that off the face right to Patel at point
fired in short on leg stump and he pulls it out to Vettori at deep backward square leg
tossed up outside off stump, driven to cover and wants the run, but hes sent back
good quicker ball spins in and he has to defend back to Patel
flat and short, back he goes, punching into the covers for one
flat down the leg side, easy pickings for Symonds, who works it into the deep for one
looped up on middle and off, Hussey goes back and defends it
flatter outside off stump, he gets forward and sweeps it around the corner for one more
good length outside off stump, run wide of gully for an easy single
back of a length on off stump, Symonds stands and drives back to Astle
back of length outside off stump now, and he runs that to gully
good length outside off stump, driven to mid-off
good length again, quicker too, and he drives back to Astle
lovely! Quicker, a tad fuller, fairly rips off the scrambled seam and squares Symonds all ends up, beating the forward prod
swept to fine leg
driven to midwicket
played to short cover for a quick single
driven to long on for a single
defended to the off side,
comes forward and defends
short in length, driven along the ground to long on&
moves back and forces to short cover, slight misfield
short in length on the pads, pushes to deep mid on for a single
nicely played, waits on the back foot and cuts late, takes on the fielder and comes back for the second run, good running
plays and misses outside the off stump, good work from McCullum
good ball defended back to the bowler
full on the legs, worked out to deep midwicket for one
slow and full on off stump, Hussey leans forward and opens the face, running to third man for one
good length delivery outside off stump, Hussey reaches for it and drives it to the sweeper cover
good length outside off stump, down comes Hussey and he picks that up nicely over extra cover for four, shot!
back of a length delivery on middle and leg, Symonds goes on the backfoot and glances it to backward square leg
good length on off stump, Symonds drives across the line but cant beat mid-on
back of a length outside off stump, run to Fulton at backward point
fuller length delivery outside the off stump, Symonds opens the face and slices that to gully
back of a length outside off stump, Hussey opens the face and collects one down to third man
fullish on leg stump, worked out to the deep midwicket fielder
back of a length, he just rocks back and punches in the gap at cover for one
good length on the stumps, he shuffles and works it to midwicket for one&
flat outside off stump, no room on offer but he opens the face very late and runs it fine

simple dismissal! An innocuous half-tracker moving away from him outside off stump, asking to be cut but what does Hussey do? He opens the face and slices that to Hamish Marshall at backward point for a dolly! McMillan gets the breakthrough, and he's cock-a-hoop
fullish outside off stump, he gets a good stride forward and defends, but is rapped on the pads, fractionally outside the line, McMillan lets out a huge appeal but Asad Rauf is unmoved
good length delivery on the stumps, White gets forward and pushes it straight to the fielder at mid-off
good length outside off stump, he opens the face and runs it to backward point
full outside the stumps, he comes forward and defends to cover
fuller length delivery down legstump, Symonds makes room slogs it away to deep square leg for four, thats the 200 for Australia
good length on middle and leg, he flicks out into the deep for one
back of a length on the stumps, he gets behind the line and defends
good length on middle and leg, worked to the onside
back of a length delivery on the middle and leg, White goes on the backfoot and flicks it away to mid wicket for a single to get off the mark
fuller length delivery angling in, Symonds shuffles across and whips it away to midwicket for a single
tossed up on the legs, Symonds gets forward and flicks to mid-on
flat on leg stump, worked into the midwicket region for one
tossed up on off stump, he gets forward and defends back down the track
tossed up on leg stump, flicked into midwicket for one
tossed up, his hard into the ground in front of cover

tossed up on middle and off, doesnt spin away much, White tries to sweep and gets rapped in front of middle, they all go up in appeal but Rauf shakes the head, too high probably, and he was very far forward....hmmm....but a damn good shout
flighted delivery outside the off stump, White kneels down and looks to slog sweep it away, misses it
flat on leg, White comes down and flicks to midwicket
flatter and quicker, he comes down but cant beat midwicket with the flick
hammered! Flat outside off stump, its time to biff it, methinks, as Symonds frees the arms and clubs it out to deep cover for four
tossed up on the stumps, Symonds comes down the track and smashes it straight down the ground for a couple, but Marshall covers good ground and makes a brilliant stop
full and down leg side, flicked around the corner and he will keep strike
flat outside off stump, he cracks that out to the sweeper
flat outside off again, and White drives into the covers
well bowled, looped up on off stump, Symonds comes down and looks to free the arms, but mistimes the slog with an inside edge to mid-on
oh boy! Its a no-ball to start with, and its got too much air on it, and White plants the front foot forward and powerfully connects with the slog, sending it miles back over wide long-on for maximum
SHOT! Tossed up again outside off stump, down goes White, sending this one well over deep midwicket for half a dozen, man can this guy hit a cricket ball
back of a length delivery on middle and leg, White goes on the backfoot and punches it to long-on for a single
looped up outside the off stump, Symonds reaches for it and drives it to sweeper cover for a single
tossed up on middle and off, he comes down and lofts it down to long-on for one
well bowled, flat on the stumps, White does well to connect this out to long-on and runs hard for the second
yorker length delivery on the stumps, White digs it out back to the bowler
flat on off stump, he makes room in an attempt to go over cover, but cant beat the fielder
theres the fifty! Flattish on middle and leg, and he easily connects with the slam and picks up four over midwicket, well played
gives it a bit more air, bad idea, and Symonds meets the ball with a murderous biff between midwicket and mid-on for four more, its paaaaarty time
fullish outside off stump, White comes forward and drives between cover and mid-off for two out to the sweeper
good ball, yorker smack on the stumps, he defends
fullish delivery angling in, White makes room in an attempt to and belt it into oblivion, but ends up with a top-edge down to third man for a couple
full outside off stump, he drives but doesnt time it cleanly, ends up with one to mid-off that brings up the 250
too full and wide outside off stump, Symonds moves away to leg and slices it square of the wicket for four, super shot
fullish delivery outside off stump, Symonds reaches for it and drives it to cover for a single
slower, back of a length ball on the stumps, which Symonds pulls out to deep midwicket for one
not what you need at this stage! A half-tracker well wide of off stump and its called wide, White just looked at it pass him and half-smiled
he oversteps, sending it down full outside off stump, White has an almighty slog across the line and ends up with a thick outside edge that runs past everyone for four to third man
terrible ball! A good length ball some three miles outside off stump, wide called duly, and thats now eight runs off one legal delivery this over...oh Bond, Bond, Bond...
back of a length outside off stump, White opens the face and runs it to third man
back of a length and angled into him, but he's made so much room outside leg stump that he can only open the face and run it to third man for one

see you later, you beauty! A good length ball outside off stump, White just frees the arms and heaves it superbly over deep midwicket, and it sails miles over the stands, hitting the roof and continuing out of the ground! Thats not coming back any time soon!
short of a length on middle and leg, White goes on the backfoot and looks to pull it away, but top-edges between mid-on and long-on for a couple
good length outside off stump, White makes room and slices that over backward point for four more, terrific batting this
fuller length delivery on off stump, Symonds comes on the frontfoot and punches it to long-off for a single
fuller on middle and leg, White shuffles across and flicks it away to deep midwicket for a couple
yorker length delivery outside the off stump, White looks to chop it away, misses it
fullish outside off stump, White drives and manages to squeeze it wide of backward point for one, well bowled
good length outside off stump, Symonds opens the arms and goes square, hitting it out to deep cover for two, McMillan does brilliantly on the ropes to save four
full outside off stump, Symonds gets forward and drives it to cover for a single
back of a length on middle and off, pulled to midwicket for one
aye aye aye, Bond! He opts for the bouncer that ends up too wide of the stumps and is called wide
gone! Bond fires it in full on the stumps and White makes room outside leg stump, looking to slog it away, but can only find McMillan at a deepish midwicket
and he gets one more! Bond bowls one on a good length outside off stump, Symonds steps to leg and looks to uppercut, but ends up nibbling it through to McCullum, thats two in two for Bond

YES he can! Bond! Short of a lengh on off stump, slower too, and it beats Bracken all ends up, cannoning into off stump, and Bond's ecstatic! Superb stuff, and boy does he love it! Huge smile, eyes twinkling like a kid's in a candy shop, arms outstretched - COME TO ME he almost says as his teammates converge on him
good length outside off stump, he hops and opens the face, running it to third man for one
full outside off stump, Johnson makes room and connects well with the inside-out drive, placing it in the gap at cover and running hard for the second, and Australia finish on 289

inn2.comm: good ball first up, movement into McCullum, who blocks it to the on side
good ball once again, almost squared him up
this time comes out of the crease and whips it behind square leg to the fence, one hand off the handle as he played that
gets behind it nicely and defends it with a straight bat
down the leg side, nudges to fine leg to pick up a single
fuller outside the off stump, comes forward and pushes to the off side
mistimes the drive to mid on
gets behind a short in length delivery and defends to the off side
good ball, a huge shout for lbw, turned down, struck the pad outside the line of the off stump
worked to the on side
pushes forward and gets an inside edge to the on side
good swing away, moves forward and defends to point
good ball swinging in from the stumps, worked to Ponting at short midwicket

caught behind, it was bit wide outside the off stump, swings away, Astle cuts at it, gets the edge, Gilchrist takes the catch... loud appeal, Astle waits for some time, asking the umpire whether it carried. The umpire gives the nod, Astle has to go. The replays are not conclusive.....
gets behind it and defends to the off side
on the pads, tucked to deep backward square leg, Fleming gets off the mark
wide outside the off stump, left alone
slower delivery, comes forward and defends
defended to point
142 km/h, left alone outside the off stump, good pace from Hilfenhaus
full and wide outside the off stump, Fleming slices it in the air to wide thirdman
comes forward to an away swinging delivery and defends to cover
plays it off his pads to square leg, fielded by White

good ball, Hilfenhaus has his first wicket in One Day International career, a straight delivery, McCullum plays across it and misses, strikes the pad in line with the off stump, loud appeal, given by umpire Harper.
pitched up delivery outside the off stump, driven well in the gap between extra-cover and mid off to the deep
defended to the off side
gets in line and defends with an open face to backward-point
runs it down to thirdman to pick up a single
short in length angled across, lets it go through to Gilchrist
gets in line on the front foot and defends with the full face off the bat to mid off
good ball on target, defends straight back down the track
lets it go outside the off stump
pushes in front of point, Clarke runs across and fields the ball
good ball short in length, defended to cover, fielded by Symonds
on middle and leg, forced to midwicket
gets the outside edge wide of the slips to thirdman
moves forward and drives firmly upto mid off
pushes to mid on for a quick single, the fielder was a bit deep, it was Hussey
good ball on target, comes forward and defends to cover
comes forward and defends to the off side
good ball angled in, nudges behind square leg to pick up a single
good shot from Taylor, width outside the off stump, moves forward and drives well to cover-point fence
on the off stump, defended to Symonds at cover
swings down the leg side, signalled wide
on the off stump line, jabbed to point
flicks it in the air over square leg fence for maximum. Good shot it was well picked up, it was full on the legs
fuller once again, driven to mid off to Hussey
good slower delivery, Taylor watches it and works to midwicket
works it from off stump to deep square leg
forces it on the up to cover, can't it get it out of the in-field
fuller on the off stump line, looking to force it through, hit straight along the ground to mid on
short in length outside the off stump, bit wide, has a waft at it and gets beaten
forces on the front foot to cover for a single
good ball on target, moves forward and pushes to mid on
moves forward and runs it down to thirdman
pushes upishly to cover, the ball seemed to have stopped on the track
142.6 km/h, left alone through to Gilchrist
short in length, plays out to point, kept a bit low
fuller on the legs, flicked in front of square leg, White in quickly prevents the single
good ball outside the off stump, walked into it, pitches and moves away, beats the outside edge
swinging away, pushes through the covers to the deep
on the off stump line, defended to point, fielded by Clarke
looking to force it down the ground, lot of bottom hand as he went for the drive, mistimes it
watchfully defended to mid off
cracking shot from Taylor, square drives it between backward-point and cover-point to the fence, lovely placement
goes after a wide delivery outside the off stump, this time he misses it, through to Gilchrist, who is standing up at the wickets
drives on the up to Symonds at covers
moves forward in line and nudges to the on side
steers it down to thirdman for a single
full toss on the legs, worked to deep midwicket
moves forward in line and defends to point
good ball outside the off stump, goes after it and gets beaten, through to Gilchrist
drives to mid on, looking for the gap, cannot find one
full and wide outside the off stump, slices it high in the air over backward-point to the fence, was looking to go down the ground.
works it behind square leg to pick up a single
short in length, stands tall in the crease and defends to cover
on the front foot defends watchfully to mid off
on the middle and leg to backward square leg, Symond fields it and throws it wide at the non-striker's end
forward defending to backward-point
pulls it on the up to midwicket fence, good shot that from Taylor
beaten outside the off stump
another good shot, lofted over midwicket, picked up quickly by Taylor, striking very well here
on the off stump, defended to cover
another beautiful shot from Taylor, it was full outside the off stump, lovely timing through to the left of backward-point to the fence. Third boundary in the over
pushes on the front foot to the off side
dabs it to backward-point, Fleming sets off for a single, sent back
on the middle and leg, nudges it behind square leg, they amble through for a single
short of a length on the off stump, defended to cover
on the off and middle, short in length worked to midwicket, Fleming was backing up, Ponting misses the stumps at the non-striker's end
short in length, Taylor lofts it high and over backward square leg, one bounce into the fence, lovely pickup
yorker length delivery, dug out back to Clark
good ball on the off stump line, bit of bat and pad to the off side
full and wide down the leg side, signalled wide
short in length, nips back in, Fleming inside edges on to the track
another good delivery short of a length, jams it down, gets the inside edge, goes over the stumps
slower delivery outside the off stump, Johnson following through as Fleming was looking for the single
looking to drive through the off side, gets a thickish edge to midwicket
good slower delivery, the off-cutter, blocked to the on side
low full toss, an attempted yorker, driven to mid on
nicely played from Taylor, works it past the short fine leg, the ball races to the fence, good wrist work.
full length delivery driven to midwicket
good yorker dug out by Taylor back to Clark, well bowled and well played
beautiful shot from Taylor, in the slot, driven straight along the ground to long on fence, Taylor playing well
full and on the legs, strikes the pads, loud appeal turned down, as the ball was going down the leg side, they go through with a leg bye
short in length, works to midwicket for a single
full on the stumps, Fleming works to deep midwicket for a single
yorker on the stumps, dug out to the on side
swings and misses outside the off stump, through to Gilchrist, gave the kitchen sink.
worked from middle and leg behind square leg
full and wide outside the off stump, Fleming looks to drive through the off side, gets the inside edge behind square leg
good shot, hoicks it over midwicket to the deep, poor running
works it behind square leg from the middle stump
short ball, Fleming drags the ball from outside the off stump, mistimes to Hayden at midwicket
good ball on the off stump line, Fleming forced to defend
slower from Bracken, the off-cutter, plays it late to thirdman to pick up a single
on the middle stump, forces down the ground to long on
low full toss outside the off stump, driven, on the bounce to Clarke at backward-point
short ball pulled around to deep midwicket, White fields the ball
gone, a soft dismissal, a slower delivery, which Fleming did not pick up,drives it in the air, Hussey moves across slightly at mid off and takes a good catch.
gets the outside edge along the ground to Hilfenhaus at thirdman
plays and misses outside the off stump, looking to force it through
full delivery driven to mid off
clips it behind square leg, fielded by Clarke
works to midwicket for a single, off the back foot
sweeps to fine leg to pick up a single
short and flat, driven off the back foot to long on
nicely forward and defends well back to Symonds
good shot from Taylor, tossed up, goes after it and drags it to square leg fence
good ball on the off stump line, stretches forward and defends on the track
on the middle and leg worked in front of square leg, Ponting moves across quickly but cannot save the single
worked nicely from the off and middle stump line to deep backward square leg, comes back for the second run, brings up Taylor's 50, well played.
defended well to cover
pulls well, drags it to deep midwicket
works a middle and leg delivery to Ponting at midwicket
bit slower from Symonds, driven down the ground to long on
works to midwicket
plays it back in the air to Symonds, did it carry... no it did not, just falls short of him
played back to the bowler
waits on the back foot and works to deep midwicket
stretches forward and looks to work it through the on side, misses, strikes the pad, loud appeal turned down, they go through with a leg bye
works it off his pads past the square leg umpire to the deep
short ball dug in, gets under it
lovely strike from Fulton, short delivery picked up nicely and pulls it well over backward square leg fence for maximum.
nudged to Ponting at midwicket
pushes on the up to deep point, fielded by Hayden
fuller delivery driven down the ground to long on, Johnson fields the ball
plays with the spin, tickled to long leg for a single
short and bit slower, driven off the back foot to long off
Shot! a slog sweep, swings it high and over the midwicket fence for maximum. Wonderful strike that from Taylor, he looks to have pulled his muscle as he went for the shot.
pulled to square leg
down the leg side, signalled wide
tossed up, another big strike, swings it high and over midwicket fence for the second six of the over, it was caught in the crowd (one-handed)
driven down the ground to long on for a single
short of a length outside off stump, and Taylor pulls across the line to mid-on
back of a length outside off stump, Fulton goes back and punches off the backfoot to covers for a quick single
fullish outside off stump and he works it across the line for one more into mid-on, all wrists on that shot
fullish down the pads, clips his back leg through to Gilchrist
short of a length outside off stump, and Fulton pulls impetuously through the line, picking up one to square leg
a good length outside off stump, Taylor walks into the shot and again whips it from outside off into square leg
good length on the stumps, worked to midwicket
good length but down the pads, and he helps it on its way around the corner for one
a shocker, very, very wide of leg stump and Gilchrist does well to take it
a tad fuller on middle and leg and he chips it into the air on the leg side, but mid-on's too deep and the ball falls safely
short of a length down leg , Fulton goes back and whips it away to backward square leg for a brace
another rubbish delivery, angled well wide of leg stump and more work for the 'keeper
much straighter this time, and he defends to the off side
again he strays to leg and Fulton works it away behind square for the single
shortish delivery just outside off stump, he rocks back and cuts into the covers for one
looped up outside off stump, Taylor cuts it late to backward point
fizzed up on off stump, Taylor plants the front pad out in front of the line and works it across into the midwicket region
back of a length on off stump, he goes back and punches down the ground
looped up outside leg stump, Fulton reaches across and then paddle-sweeps it around the corner, deftly done
short and wide, spinning away from him, and he rocks back and slaps it backward of point for four, good timing and placement
back of a length on middle and off, he goes back and drives straight to mid-on
back of a length again, this time he punches back to the bowler
fuller this time, looks like the offcutter, which he works past square leg with ease
good length this time, slower ball, and Fulton gets forward and drives back to Hilfenhaus on the bounce
dragged in short, Fulton swivels quickly and pulls through square leg and midwicket, Hayden out in the deep runs forward and dives, right-hand outstretched, but gets no where near it and thats four
fuller length delivery angling in, Fulton gets right behind and looks to defend it, inside edge onto the pads
tossed up on the stumps, defended back
bad ball, wide down leg stump
looped up outside the line of leg stump, Taylor slog sweeps but cant connect, and grimaces after missing the shot

looped up on off stump, Taylor gets into position to slog sweep it again, doesnt time it all that well, getting under it, but has enough forearm power to heave it over deep midwicket for half a dozen, that ball was in the air for a long, long time
drifts down the legs and its worked to square leg for one
straighter delivery on the stumps, Fulton plays it back to the bowler
flattish delivery on leg strump, Fulton shuffles across and glances it to backward square leg
fullish outside off stump and he works it across the line, flicking in the air just wide of Ponting at midwicket
back of a length on middle and leg, Fulton goes on the backfoot and punches to mid-on
fuller length delivery outside the off stump, he leans into the shot and drives it out to extra cover
another attempted off cutter becomes a low full toss which Taylor doesnt pick at all, and is lucky not to chop onto his stumps
good length outside off stump, again he drives across the line uppishly into mid-on for the single
good length delivery outside off stump, Fulton reaches for it and drives it to short cover

and he strikes first ball! A good length-quick delivery angled across him outside off stump, and Taylor obliges with a flashy drive that takes the regulation outside edge into a diving Gilchrist's gloves, good breakthrough to end a good innings
and he's greeted by a bad ball, very, very full and wide of off stump
better one, a good length delivery that angles past his tame front-foot prod, almost missed kissing the edge of the bat
back of a length outside off stump, played out to backward point
slower and a bit fuller, his feet dont really go anywhere and he closes the face of the bat as he defends back to Johnson
good length on off stump, again he anxiously plays it back to Johnson, but the head and eyes were headed somewhere else
short of a length outside off stump, played out past backward point with some confidence this time
back of a length on middle and off, Fulton goes back and drives to mid-on
rolls the fingers over it, getting to full on off stump, Fulton whips that across the line into mid-wicket
good length on the stumps, driven back down the ground and he fields with the outstretched right hand

low full toss on off stump, he flicks across the line past midwicket, quickly comes Clarke from the deep, who moves, picks it up and throws it straight onto the nonstriker's end, and gets his man! He didnt have a lot to work with, moving and throwing it on the turn, and looking at one stump, but his brilliance does the rest! McMillan cant believe it, and man, that was some throw
fullish on off stump, and he flicks it into midwicket for one
good length on the stumps, Vettori gets behind the line and defends, uneasily
back of a length on off stump, he drives and gets an inside-edge to the on side

another one bites the dust! Back of a good length delivery, very innocuous, it must be said, and Fulton drives off the backfoot in the air above Symonds at short extra cover, who jumps up and gets a hand to it, just parrying it up in the air and holding it easily on the second attempt&
good length outside off stump, he watches it carefully and shoulders arms
back of a length on middle and off, he plays loosely at it and ends up running it to backward point
back of a length outside off stump, Franklin punches to Ponting at cover
slightly shorter this time, and he hops and punches off the backfoot to mid-off
from around the wicket to the left-hander, looped up and he flicks to mid-on
flat outside off stump, driven to point
flatter trajectory on middle and off, Vettori shuffles and turns it fine for one
tossed up, Franklin drives back to Symonds, who fields well moving to his left
tossed up outside off stump, and he drives in the gap at cover for one
back of a length delivery on middle and leg, Vettori goes on the backfoot and glances it to short fine leg
strives for the yorker but its in the wrong spot, and Franklin drives to mid-off
good length outside off stump, he stands and goes fishing, just wafting the bat at it

as the run rate soars, Vettori chances his arm but holes out to deep square leg! Clark drops one in short of a length on middle and leg, and Vettori swivels and chips it off the pads in the air out to deep square leg, where Hayden, moving from a deepish mid-wicket, covers ground and holds a relatively easy catch
good length on middle and leg, he flicks around the corner out to Hilfenhaus at fine leg for one
slower ball, on a fullish length on off stump, and he drives back to Clark

back of a length just outside off stump, Bond defends away from his body and the outside edge runs along the ground to third man, looked like he may have intentionally played it late with the open face, but who's to say, its a tail-ender, after all
tossed up outside off stump, driven to cover
good length delivery outside off stump, Bond comes on the frontfoot and shoulders arms to it
flattish outside off stump, driven to the offside and Symonds fields himself
gives it some more air on off stump, and its flicked to mid-on

bowled 'em! Gives it some air, rolling the fingers over it, but it comes out faster than Bond expected, and he plays all over it as the ball quickly slides between pat and pad and disturbs the furniture
tossed up outside off stump, and Gillespie presents a quite impressive front foot defence to that delivery

and like Johnson a few overs ago, he picks up one with his first ball! Looped up out of the back of the hand, its the wrong 'un, and Franklin, looking for the spin, drives across the line and ends up with a leading edge to Clarke at a shortish point, and Australia are now a wicket away from victory
quicker delivery on the stumps, Patel gets right behind and defends it solidly
spinning down leg stump, Patel shuffles and tries to dab it fine, but leg byes are signalled
looped up on middle and leg, Gillespie kneels down and sweeps it away to fine leg for a brace
fullish delivery on leg stump, he gets forward and flicks it away to backward square leg for a couple more
quicker through the air, and full outside leg stump, Gillespie looks to flick but the ball dips on him and he falls over in the shot
fullish on off stump, flicked to midwicket, no chance of a run
tossed up outside off stump, and the No. 11 just picks that up and slams it over mid-on for four

thats the end of that! Symonds tosses it up invitingly outside off stump, Patel gets a half-stride forward and lofts it down the ground high, high in the air, and Hilfenhaus at long-on squints against the sun and gets under it, holding a neat catch to round off a comprehensive Australian victory
